Diagnosis
. 

Parvoscincus decipiens

can be diagnosed by the following combination of characters: (
1
) A small body size (SVL at maturity 
35.02–40.62 mm
); (
2
) MBSR = 
30–34
; (
3
) PV = 
54–63
; (
4
) dorsal scales non-striated without apical pits; (
5
) apical pits on hind limbs, variably present on forelimbs; (
6
) four enlarged supraoculars; (
7
) anterior loreal single; (
8
) three preoculars; (
9
) and 
14–18
Toe IV SDL.
